2026-02-20 07:03:57 - INFO - 716 -{"tools": [], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are an expert Travel Planner assistant specializing in creating detailed holiday itineraries.\n\nYour role is to:\n1. Create a comprehensive day-by-day travel plan based on the user's destination country and number of days\n2. Suggest popular tourist attractions and activities for each day\n3. Recommend suitable hotels with different budget categories (budget, mid-range, luxury)\n4. Calculate approximate budget breakdown including:\n   - Accommodation costs per night\n   - Daily food expenses\n   - Transportation costs\n   - Attraction entry fees\n   - Total estimated trip cost\n\nInput from user: Country/City and Number of Days\n\nOutput format:\n- Day-by-day itinerary with morning, afternoon, and evening activities\n- Hotel suggestions with approximate prices\n- Budget calculator with itemized costs\n- Travel tips and recommendations\n\nBe specific, practical, and provide realistic time estimates for each activity.", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "I want to two day trip to goa with the budget of 50000. Can you help me plan it?"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway \u2013 INR\u202f50,000 (for 1 adult)\n\nBelow is a ready\u2011to\u2011go plan that balances beach time, culture, good food and a little adventure while staying comfortably within a **\u20b950\u202f000** budget.  \nAll times are approximate and can be shifted a little to suit your pace or the season.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udcc5 DAY\u2011BY\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \n\n| Day | Time | Activity | Details & Approx. Cost |\n|-----|------|----------|------------------------|\n| **Day\u202f1 \u2013 North Goa** | **08:00\u202f\u2013\u202f09:00** | **Arrival & Check\u2011in** | Fly into Dabolim (GOI) or arrive by train/bus. Drop luggage at hotel. |\n| | **09:00\u202f\u2013\u202f10:30** | **Breakfast & Beach Walk** | Breakfast at **Caf\u00e9 Chocolatti** (Panjim) \u2013 \u20b9250. Walk along **Miramar Beach** for sunrise. |\n| | **10:30\u202f\u2013\u202f12:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | Entry \u20b920. Great photo spots; enjoy sea\u2011view from the lighthouse. |\n| | **12:30\u202f\u2013\u202f13:30** | **Lunch** | **Mum\u2019s Kitchen** (Goan thali) \u2013 \u20b9350. |\n| | **13:30\u202f\u2013\u202f15:30** | **Calangute & Baga Beaches** | Sun\u2011bathing, optional water\u2011sport (parasailing \u20b9800). |\n| | **15:30\u202f\u2013\u202f16:00** | **Coffee Break** | **Caf\u00e9 Bodega** \u2013 iced coffee \u20b9150. |\n| | **16:00\u202f\u2013\u202f18:00** | **Anjuna Flea Market** (Sat\u2011Sun only) | Souvenirs, jewellery, handicrafts. No entry fee; budget \u20b9500 for shopping. |\n| | **18:00\u202f\u2013\u202f19:30** | **Sunset at Chapora Fort** | Walk up to the fort (free). Famous \u201cDil Chahta Hai\u201d view. |\n| | **19:30\u202f\u2013\u202f21:30** | **Dinner & Nightlife** | Dinner at **Thalassa** (Greek/Seafood) \u2013 \u20b91\u202f200. End with a cocktail at **Club Cabana** (optional) \u2013 \u20b9800. |\n| | **21:30\u202f\u2013\u202f22:30** | **Return to Hotel** | Relax, maybe a night\u2011cap at the hotel bar. |\n| **Day\u202f2 \u2013 South Goa** | **08:00\u202f\u2013\u202f09:00** | **Breakfast** | Hotel buffet (mid\u2011range) \u2013 included; budget option: **Caf\u00e9 Central** \u2013 \u20b9200. |\n| | **09:00\u202f\u2013\u202f11:00** | **Old Goa Churches** | **Basilica of Bom\u202fJesus** (free, donation \u20b950) & **Se Cathedral** (free). |\n| | **11:00\u202f\u2013\u202f12:30** | **Museum of Christian Art** | Entry \u20b9150. |\n| | **12:30\u202f\u2013\u202f13:30** | **Lunch** | **Martin\u2019s Corner** (seafood) \u2013 \u20b9600. |\n| | **13:30\u202f\u2013\u202f15:30** | **Colva / Benaulim Beach** | Relax, try a beach shack for fresh coconut water (\u20b980). |\n| | **15:30\u202f\u2013\u202f16:30** | **Dudhsagar Waterfall Day\u2011Trip (optional)** | If you love nature, take a shared jeep (\u20b91\u202f200 round\u2011trip) + entry \u20b930 + boat ride \u20b9250. Otherwise, skip and enjoy **Palolem Beach** (free). |\n| | **16:30\u202f\u2013\u202f18:00** | **Spice Plantation Tour** | **Sahakari Spice Farm** \u2013 guided tour & tea tasting \u20b9350. |\n| | **18:00\u202f\u2013\u202f19:30** | **Sunset at Palolem** (if you skipped Dudhsagar) | Walk along the crescent\u2011shaped beach. |\n| | **19:30\u202f\u2013\u202f21:00** | **Dinner** | **Fisherman\u2019s Wharf** (Goan cuisine) \u2013 \u20b91\u202f200. |\n| | **21:00\u202f\u2013\u202f22:00** | **Evening Stroll & Return** | Head back to hotel, collect luggage. |\n| | **22:30** | **Departure** | Transfer to Dabolim Airport / railway station. |\n\n> **Total active sightseeing time each day \u2248\u202f8\u20119\u202fhrs** \u2013 enough to see the highlights without feeling rushed.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83c\udfe8 HOTEL SUGGESTIONS (per night, double\u2011occupancy)\n\n| Category | Property (North) | Property (South) | Approx. Nightly Rate (\u20b9) | What\u2019s Included |\n|----------|------------------|------------------|--------------------------|-----------------|\n| **Budget** | **Zostel Goa \u2013 Calangute** | **The Fern Residency \u2013 Palolem** | 1,500 \u2013 2,200 | 2\u2011bed dorm or private twin, free Wi\u2011Fi, rooftop lounge, locker |\n| **Mid\u2011range** | **Casa De Goa \u2013 Panjim** (heritage boutique) | **The LaLiT Golf & Spa Resort \u2013 Canacona** | 4,500 \u2013 6,500 | Air\u2011cond rooms, breakfast, pool, easy beach access |\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa \u2013 Benaulim** | **Alila Diwa Goa \u2013 Majorda** | 12,000 \u2013 15,000 | 5\u2011star service, private beach, spa, multiple dining venues |\n\n*Pick one property and stay the whole trip (2 nights). The budget calculations below use the **mid\u2011range** option (\u20b95,500/night). Swap in budget or luxury rates to see how the total changes.*\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udcb0 BUDGET CALCULATOR (\u20b9\u202fINR)\n\n| Item | Cost (per person) | Notes |\n|------|-------------------|-------|\n| **Accommodation (2 nights)** | 5,500\u202f\u00d7\u202f2 = **11,000** | Mid\u2011range hotel; budget option would be ~3,200, luxury ~26,000 |\n| **Food & Drinks** | Breakfast (included) + Lunch \u20b9600\u202f\u00d7\u202f2 + Dinner \u20b91,200\u202f\u00d7\u202f2 + Snacks/coffee \u20b9300\u202f\u00d7\u202f2 = **4,200** |\n| **Local Transportation** | Airport\u2011hotel taxi (\u20b9800 each way) = 1,600 <br> Scooter rental (\u20b9350\u202f\u00d7\u202f2) = 700 <br> Shared jeep to Dudhsagar (optional) = 1,200 | **Total (with waterfall)** = **3,500**; without waterfall = **2,300** |\n| **Attraction Fees** | Fort Aguada 20, Museum 150, Spice Farm 350, Church donations 100, Boat ride Dudhsagar 250, Misc. (parking, water) 200 = **1,070** |\n| **Shopping / Souvenirs** | Approx. **1,000** (handicrafts, beachwear) |\n| **Miscellaneous (tips, emergency cash)** | **500** |\n| **Grand Total (mid\u2011range, with Dudhsagar)** | **21,770** |\n| **Grand Total (mid\u2011range, without Dudhsagar)** | **20,570** |\n| **Remaining buffer (\u20b9\u202f50,000 \u2013 total)** | **\u2248\u202f28,000** | Plenty of room for upgrades (luxury stay, extra activities, night\u2011life, or a second traveler). |\n\n> **If you choose the budget hotels** the total drops to ~\u20b9\u202f13\u202f000, leaving **\u20b9\u202f37\u202f000** for extra indulgences.  \n> **If you opt for luxury** the total rises to ~\u20b9\u202f44\u202f000 (still under \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000) \u2013 you could even add a private yacht sunset cruise (\u2248\u20b9\u202f6\u202f000) and stay within budget.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udeeb QUICK LOGISTICS\n\n| Item | Details |\n|------|---------|\n| **Getting there** | Fly into **Dabolim (GOI)** \u2013 many low\u2011cost carriers (IndiGo, SpiceJet). From Mumbai \u2192 ~1\u202fh 15\u202fmin flight (\u20b9\u202f3\u202f000\u20114\u202f500). |\n| **Airport\u2011to\u2011hotel transfer** | Pre\u2011book a **Goa Airport Taxi** (\u20b9\u202f800\u20111,000) or use **Ola/Uber**. |\n| **Getting around** | **Scooter rental** is the cheapest & most flexible (\u20b9\u202f350\u2011400/day). Carry a helmet! <br>For longer trips (e.g., Dudhsagar) use shared jeeps or book a day\u2011tour (\u20b9\u202f1\u202f200\u20111\u202f500). |\n| **Best time to visit** | **Oct\u2011Mar** (cool, dry). Avoid monsoon (Jun\u2011Sep) unless you love waterfalls. |\n| **What to pack** | Light cottons, swimwear, flip\u2011flops, sunscreen (SPF\u202f30+), hat, reusable water bottle, small day\u2011backpack, waterproof phone pouch. |\n| **Safety tips** | Keep an eye on belongings on busy beaches/markets. Drink bottled water. Night\u2011time beach walks are safe in popular zones (Baga, Calangute). |\n\n---\n\n## \ud83c\udf89 FINAL RECOMMENDATIONS\n\n1. **Book accommodation early** (especially for the high\u2011season Dec\u2011Jan). The mid\u2011range hotels listed have excellent reviews and are centrally located.\n2. **Reserve a scooter** online (many providers allow advance payment) to guarantee availability.\n3. **If you love nightlife**, swap the dinner at Thalassa (Day\u202f1) for a beach\u2011side party at **Tito\u2019s** or **Mambo\u2019s** \u2013 extra \u20b9\u202f500\u2011800.\n4. **For a romantic touch**, add a **sunset dolphin\u2011watching cruise** from Palolem (\u2248\u20b9\u202f1\u202f200 per person) \u2013 fits comfortably within the remaining budget.\n5. **Keep a small cash reserve** (\u20b9\u202f2\u202f000\u20113\u202f000) for tips and occasional cash\u2011only stalls.\n\nEnjoy your Goa adventure \u2013 sun, sea, spice, and smiles await! \ud83c\udf1e\ud83c\udfd6\ufe0f\ud83d\udea4"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Travel_Researcher", "content": "Error occured in python script name [C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_TravelBot\\HolidayAgent\\Tools\\TavilyTool.py] line number [11] error message [HolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail']"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-3125b298-a6b0-4825-99c5-2db3e3c532cd", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "stop", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": "I\u2019m sorry you ran into that error \u2013 let\u2019s troubleshoot it together.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udd0e What the traceback is telling us\n\n```\nHolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail'\n```\n\n* The class **`HolidayAgentException`** is defined with an `__init__` method that expects **two** arguments:\n  1. `message` (or whatever you named the first parameter)  \n  2. `error_detail`\n\n* Somewhere in **`TavilyTool.py`** (line\u202f11) the code raises the exception **without** supplying the second argument, so Python raises a `TypeError`.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udcc2 Typical definition (what it probably looks like)\n\n```python\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, message: str, error_detail: str):\n        super().__init__(message)\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n```\n\nIf you raise it like this:\n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Failed to fetch data\")\n```\n\nyou\u2019ll get the exact error you saw because `error_detail` is missing.\n\n---\n\n## \u2705 How to fix it\n\n### 1\ufe0f\u20e3 Add the missing argument wherever the exception is raised\n\n**Before (problematic)**  \n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Failed to fetch data\")\n```\n\n**After (fixed)**  \n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\n    \"Failed to fetch data\",\n    error_detail=f\"Status code {response.status_code}\"   # or any string that helps debug\n)\n```\n\nYou can pass any string that gives more context \u2013 e.g., the HTTP status code, the URL that was called, or the original exception message.\n\n### 2\ufe0f\u20e3 If you want the second argument to be optional\n\nModify the exception class so that `error_detail` has a default value:\n\n```python\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, message: str, error_detail: str = \"\"):\n        super().__init__(message)\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n```\n\nNow you can raise it with just the message, and `error_detail` will default to an empty string.\n\n### 3\ufe0f\u20e3 Verify the raise location (line\u202f11)\n\nOpen **`C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_TravelBot\\HolidayAgent\\Tools\\TavilyTool.py`** and look at line\u202f11. It will likely be something like:\n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Tavily API request failed\")\n```\n\nReplace it with the fixed version (or make the exception class optional as shown above).\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Quick \u201cpatch\u201d you can copy\u2011paste\n\nIf you prefer a minimal change, just edit the exception class:\n\n```python\n# ---- at the top of TavilyTool.py (or wherever the class is defined) ----\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Custom exception for the HolidayAgent tools.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, message: str, error_detail: str = \"\"):\n        # Call the base class constructor with the message\n        super().__init__(message)\n        # Store any extra detail for logging / debugging\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        # Show both parts when the exception is printed\n        base = super().__str__()\n        return f\"{base} | Detail: {self.error_detail}\" if self.error_detail else base\n```\n\nNow any existing `raise HolidayAgentException(\"\u2026\")` calls will work, and you still have the option to pass a detailed string when you need it.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udccb Next steps for you\n\n1. **Open the file** `C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_TravelBot\\HolidayAgent\\Tools\\TavilyTool.py`.\n2. **Locate line\u202f11** (or any `raise HolidayAgentException` statements).\n3. **Either**  \n   * add a second argument (recommended when you have useful debug info), **or**  \n   * change the class definition to make `error_detail` optional (as shown above).\n4. **Save** the file and re\u2011run your script.\n\nIf you still see an error, please copy\u2011paste t