ail=f\\\"Status {response.status_code} \u2013 URL {url}\\\"\\n  )\\n  ```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \u2705 Checklist after applying the patch\\n\\n1. **Open the file** and replace the old class definition with the snippet above.  \\n2. **Save** the file.  \\n3. **Run** your script again.  \\n   * If the exception is raised, you\u2019ll now see a clear message like:  \\n     ```\\n     HolidayAgentException: Tavily API request failed | Detail: Status 504 \u2013 URL https://api.tavily.com/\u2026\\n     ```\\n   * If the request succeeds, the script proceeds without the `TypeError`.  \\n4. (Optional) If you want logs written to a file, configure logging in your main module, e.g.:\\n\\n   ```python\\n   import logging\\n   logging.basicConfig(\\n       filename='holiday_agent.log',\\n       level=logging.ERROR,\\n       format='%(asctime)s %(levelname)s %(name)s %(message)s'\\n   )\\n   ```\\n\\n5. **Test both paths**:  \\n   * Force an error (e.g., disconnect internet) to see the detailed log.  \\n   * Run a normal request to confirm nothing else breaks.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 What to do next?\\n\\n* **If you still see an error**, copy the *exact* traceback (including line numbers) and the surrounding code (the raise line and the class definition) and paste it here \u2013 I\u2019ll help you troubleshoot further.  \\n* **If you want to enrich the error detail**, consider passing the original exception message:\\n\\n  ```python\\n  try:\\n      response = requests.get(url, timeout=10)\\n      response.raise_for_status()\\n  except requests.RequestException as exc:\\n      raise HolidayAgentException(\\n          \\\"Tavily API request failed\\\",\\n          error_detail=str(exc)\\n      )\\n  ```\\n\\n* **If you\u2019d like a tiny wrapper** around the Tavily API that automatically catches and re\u2011raises with this custom exception, let me know and I can sketch that out for you.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### TL;DR\\n- **Root cause:** `HolidayAgentException` required two args but was called with one.  \\n- **Fix:** Make `error_detail` optional (default `\\\"\\\"`) or always pass a second argument.  \\n- **Implementation:** Replace the class definition with the snippet above; no other code changes needed.\\n\\nGive it a run and tell me how it goes! \ud83c\udf89\",\"type\":\"TextMessage\"},\"inner_messages\":[]},\"name\":\"Travel_Planner\"}", "sender": "Travel_Planner_053ed073-56ef-4d41-97ec-9b5a7272d1b7/053ed073-56ef-4d41-97ec-9b5a7272d1b7", "receiver": "group_topic_053ed073-56ef-4d41-97ec-9b5a7272d1b7/053ed073-56ef-4d41-97ec-9b5a7272d1b7", "kind": "MessageKind.PUBLISH", "delivery_stage": "DeliveryStage.SEND", "type": "Message"}
