2026-02-20 07:08:32 - INFO - 716 -{"tools": [], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are an expert Travel Planner assistant specializing in creating detailed holiday itineraries.\n\nYour role is to:\n1. Create a comprehensive day-by-day travel plan based on the user's destination country and number of days\n2. Suggest popular tourist attractions and activities for each day\n3. Recommend suitable hotels with different budget categories (budget, mid-range, luxury)\n4. Calculate approximate budget breakdown including:\n   - Accommodation costs per night\n   - Daily food expenses\n   - Transportation costs\n   - Attraction entry fees\n   - Total estimated trip cost\n\nInput from user: Country/City and Number of Days\n\nOutput format:\n- Day-by-day itinerary with morning, afternoon, and evening activities\n- Hotel suggestions with approximate prices\n- Budget calculator with itemized costs\n- Travel tips and recommendations\n\nBe specific, practical, and provide realistic time estimates for each activity.", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "I want to two day trip to goa with the budget of 50000. Can you help me plan it?"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway \u2013 INR\u202f50,000 (for 1 adult)\n\nBelow is a ready\u2011to\u2011go plan that balances beach time, culture, good food and a little adventure while staying comfortably within a **\u20b950\u202f000** budget.  \nAll times are approximate and can be shifted a little to suit your pace or the season.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udcc5 DAY\u2011BY\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \n\n| Day | Time | Activity | Details & Approx. Cost |\n|-----|------|----------|------------------------|\n| **Day\u202f1 \u2013 North Goa** | **08:00\u202f\u2013\u202f09:00** | **Arrival & Check\u2011in** | Fly into Dabolim (GOI) or arrive by train/bus. Drop luggage at hotel. |\n| | **09:00\u202f\u2013\u202f10:30** | **Breakfast & Beach Walk** | Breakfast at **Caf\u00e9 Chocolatti** (Panjim) \u2013 \u20b9250. Walk along **Miramar Beach** for sunrise. |\n| | **10:30\u202f\u2013\u202f12:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | Entry \u20b920. Great photo spots; enjoy sea\u2011view from the lighthouse. |\n| | **12:30\u202f\u2013\u202f13:30** | **Lunch** | **Mum\u2019s Kitchen** (Goan thali) \u2013 \u20b9350. |\n| | **13:30\u202f\u2013\u202f15:30** | **Calangute & Baga Beaches** | Sun\u2011bathing, optional water\u2011sport (parasailing \u20b9800). |\n| | **15:30\u202f\u2013\u202f16:00** | **Coffee Break** | **Caf\u00e9 Bodega** \u2013 iced coffee \u20b9150. |\n| | **16:00\u202f\u2013\u202f18:00** | **Anjuna Flea Market** (Sat\u2011Sun only) | Souvenirs, jewellery, handicrafts. No entry fee; budget \u20b9500 for shopping. |\n| | **18:00\u202f\u2013\u202f19:30** | **Sunset at Chapora Fort** | Walk up to the fort (free). Famous \u201cDil Chahta Hai\u201d view. |\n| | **19:30\u202f\u2013\u202f21:30** | **Dinner & Nightlife** | Dinner at **Thalassa** (Greek/Seafood) \u2013 \u20b91\u202f200. End with a cocktail at **Club Cabana** (optional) \u2013 \u20b9800. |\n| | **21:30\u202f\u2013\u202f22:30** | **Return to Hotel** | Relax, maybe a night\u2011cap at the hotel bar. |\n| **Day\u202f2 \u2013 South Goa** | **08:00\u202f\u2013\u202f09:00** | **Breakfast** | Hotel buffet (mid\u2011range) \u2013 included; budget option: **Caf\u00e9 Central** \u2013 \u20b9200. |\n| | **09:00\u202f\u2013\u202f11:00** | **Old Goa Churches** | **Basilica of Bom\u202fJesus** (free, donation \u20b950) & **Se Cathedral** (free). |\n| | **11:00\u202f\u2013\u202f12:30** | **Museum of Christian Art** | Entry \u20b9150. |\n| | **12:30\u202f\u2013\u202f13:30** | **Lunch** | **Martin\u2019s Corner** (seafood) \u2013 \u20b9600. |\n| | **13:30\u202f\u2013\u202f15:30** | **Colva / Benaulim Beach** | Relax, try a beach shack for fresh coconut water (\u20b980). |\n| | **15:30\u202f\u2013\u202f16:30** | **Dudhsagar Waterfall Day\u2011Trip (optional)** | If you love nature, take a shared jeep (\u20b91\u202f200 round\u2011trip) + entry \u20b930 + boat ride \u20b9250. Otherwise, skip and enjoy **Palolem Beach** (free). |\n| | **16:30\u202f\u2013\u202f18:00** | **Spice Plantation Tour** | **Sahakari Spice Farm** \u2013 guided tour & tea tasting \u20b9350. |\n| | **18:00\u202f\u2013\u202f19:30** | **Sunset at Palolem** (if you skipped Dudhsagar) | Walk along the crescent\u2011shaped beach. |\n| | **19:30\u202f\u2013\u202f21:00** | **Dinner** | **Fisherman\u2019s Wharf** (Goan cuisine) \u2013 \u20b91\u202f200. |\n| | **21:00\u202f\u2013\u202f22:00** | **Evening Stroll & Return** | Head back to hotel, collect luggage. |\n| | **22:30** | **Departure** | Transfer to Dabolim Airport / railway station. |\n\n> **Total active sightseeing time each day \u2248\u202f8\u20119\u202fhrs** \u2013 enough to see the highlights without feeling rushed.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83c\udfe8 HOTEL SUGGESTIONS (per night, double\u2011occupancy)\n\n| Category | Property (North) | Property (South) | Approx. Nightly Rate (\u20b9) | What\u2019s Included |\n|----------|------------------|------------------|--------------------------|-----------------|\n| **Budget** | **Zostel Goa \u2013 Calangute** | **The Fern Residency \u2013 Palolem** | 1,500 \u2013 2,200 | 2\u2011bed dorm or private twin, free Wi\u2011Fi, rooftop lounge, locker |\n| **Mid\u2011range** | **Casa De Goa \u2013 Panjim** (heritage boutique) | **The LaLiT Golf & Spa Resort \u2013 Canacona** | 4,500 \u2013 6,500 | Air\u2011cond rooms, breakfast, pool, easy beach access |\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa \u2013 Benaulim** | **Alila Diwa Goa \u2013 Majorda** | 12,000 \u2013 15,000 | 5\u2011star service, private beach, spa, multiple dining venues |\n\n*Pick one property and stay the whole trip (2 nights). The budget calculations below use the **mid\u2011range** option (\u20b95,500/night). Swap in budget or luxury rates to see how the total changes.*\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udcb0 BUDGET CALCULATOR (\u20b9\u202fINR)\n\n| Item | Cost (per person) | Notes |\n|------|-------------------|-------|\n| **Accommodation (2 nights)** | 5,500\u202f\u00d7\u202f2 = **11,000** | Mid\u2011range hotel; budget option would be ~3,200, luxury ~26,000 |\n| **Food & Drinks** | Breakfast (included) + Lunch \u20b9600\u202f\u00d7\u202f2 + Dinner \u20b91,200\u202f\u00d7\u202f2 + Snacks/coffee \u20b9300\u202f\u00d7\u202f2 = **4,200** |\n| **Local Transportation** | Airport\u2011hotel taxi (\u20b9800 each way) = 1,600 <br> Scooter rental (\u20b9350\u202f\u00d7\u202f2) = 700 <br> Shared jeep to Dudhsagar (optional) = 1,200 | **Total (with waterfall)** = **3,500**; without waterfall = **2,300** |\n| **Attraction Fees** | Fort Aguada 20, Museum 150, Spice Farm 350, Church donations 100, Boat ride Dudhsagar 250, Misc. (parking, water) 200 = **1,070** |\n| **Shopping / Souvenirs** | Approx. **1,000** (handicrafts, beachwear) |\n| **Miscellaneous (tips, emergency cash)** | **500** |\n| **Grand Total (mid\u2011range, with Dudhsagar)** | **21,770** |\n| **Grand Total (mid\u2011range, without Dudhsagar)** | **20,570** |\n| **Remaining buffer (\u20b9\u202f50,000 \u2013 total)** | **\u2248\u202f28,000** | Plenty of room for upgrades (luxury stay, extra activities, night\u2011life, or a second traveler). |\n\n> **If you choose the budget hotels** the total drops to ~\u20b9\u202f13\u202f000, leaving **\u20b9\u202f37\u202f000** for extra indulgences.  \n> **If you opt for luxury** the total rises to ~\u20b9\u202f44\u202f000 (still under \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000) \u2013 you could even add a private yacht sunset cruise (\u2248\u20b9\u202f6\u202f000) and stay within budget.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udeeb QUICK LOGISTICS\n\n| Item | Details |\n|------|---------|\n| **Getting there** | Fly into **Dabolim (GOI)** \u2013 many low\u2011cost carriers (IndiGo, SpiceJet). From Mumbai \u2192 ~1\u202fh 15\u202fmin flight (\u20b9\u202f3\u202f000\u20114\u202f500). |\n| **Airport\u2011to\u2011hotel transfer** | Pre\u2011book a **Goa Airport Taxi** (\u20b9\u202f800\u20111,000) or use **Ola/Uber**. |\n| **Getting around** | **Scooter rental** is the cheapest & most flexible (\u20b9\u202f350\u2011400/day). Carry a helmet! <br>For longer trips (e.g., Dudhsagar) use shared jeeps or book a day\u2011tour (\u20b9\u202f1\u202f200\u20111\u202f500). |\n| **Best time to visit** | **Oct\u2011Mar** (cool, dry). Avoid monsoon (Jun\u2011Sep) unless you love waterfalls. |\n| **What to pack** | Light cottons, swimwear, flip\u2011flops, sunscreen (SPF\u202f30+), hat, reusable water bottle, small day\u2011backpack, waterproof phone pouch. |\n| **Safety tips** | Keep an eye on belongings on busy beaches/markets. Drink bottled water. Night\u2011time beach walks are safe in popular zones (Baga, Calangute). |\n\n---\n\n## \ud83c\udf89 FINAL RECOMMENDATIONS\n\n1. **Book accommodation early** (especially for the high\u2011season Dec\u2011Jan). The mid\u2011range hotels listed have excellent reviews and are centrally located.\n2. **Reserve a scooter** online (many providers allow advance payment) to guarantee availability.\n3. **If you love nightlife**, swap the dinner at Thalassa (Day\u202f1) for a beach\u2011side party at **Tito\u2019s** or **Mambo\u2019s** \u2013 extra \u20b9\u202f500\u2011800.\n4. **For a romantic touch**, add a **sunset dolphin\u2011watching cruise** from Palolem (\u2248\u20b9\u202f1\u202f200 per person) \u2013 fits comfortably within the remaining budget.\n5. **Keep a small cash reserve** (\u20b9\u202f2\u202f000\u20113\u202f000) for tips and occasional cash\u2011only stalls.\n\nEnjoy your Goa adventure \u2013 sun, sea, spice, and smiles await! \ud83c\udf1e\ud83c\udfd6\ufe0f\ud83d\udea4"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Travel_Researcher", "content": "Error occured in python script name [C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_TravelBot\\HolidayAgent\\Tools\\TavilyTool.py] line number [11] error message [HolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail']"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "I\u2019m sorry you ran into that error \u2013 let\u2019s troubleshoot it together.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udd0e What the traceback is telling us\n\n```\nHolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail'\n```\n\n* The class **`HolidayAgentException`** is defined with an `__init__` method that expects **two** arguments:\n  1. `message` (or whatever you named the first parameter)  \n  2. `error_detail`\n\n* Somewhere in **`TavilyTool.py`** (line\u202f11) the code raises the exception **without** supplying the second argument, so Python raises a `TypeError`.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udcc2 Typical definition (what it probably looks like)\n\n```python\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, message: str, error_detail: str):\n        super().__init__(message)\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n```\n\nIf you raise it like this:\n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Failed to fetch data\")\n```\n\nyou\u2019ll get the exact error you saw because `error_detail` is missing.\n\n---\n\n## \u2705 How to fix it\n\n### 1\ufe0f\u20e3 Add the missing argument wherever the exception is raised\n\n**Before (problematic)**  \n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Failed to fetch data\")\n```\n\n**After (fixed)**  \n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\n    \"Failed to fetch data\",\n    error_detail=f\"Status code {response.status_code}\"   # or any string that helps debug\n)\n```\n\nYou can pass any string that gives more context \u2013 e.g., the HTTP status code, the URL that was called, or the original exception message.\n\n### 2\ufe0f\u20e3 If you want the second argument to be optional\n\nModify the exception class so that `error_detail` has a default value:\n\n```python\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, message: str, error_detail: str = \"\"):\n        super().__init__(message)\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n```\n\nNow you can raise it with just the message, and `error_detail` will default to an empty string.\n\n### 3\ufe0f\u20e3 Verify the raise location (line\u202f11)\n\nOpen **`C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_TravelBot\\HolidayAgent\\Tools\\TavilyTool.py`** and look at line\u202f11. It will likely be something like:\n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Tavily API request failed\")\n```\n\nReplace it with the fixed version (or make the exception class optional as shown above).\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Quick \u201cpatch\u201d you can copy\u2011paste\n\nIf you prefer a minimal change, just edit the exception class:\n\n```python\n# ---- at the top of TavilyTool.py (or wherever the class is defined) ----\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Custom exception for the HolidayAgent tools.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, message: str, error_detail: str = \"\"):\n        # Call the base class constructor with the message\n        super().__init__(message)\n        # Store any extra detail for logging / debugging\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        # Show both parts when the exception is printed\n        base = super().__str__()\n        return f\"{base} | Detail: {self.error_detail}\" if self.error_detail else base\n```\n\nNow any existing `raise HolidayAgentException(\"\u2026\")` calls will work, and you still have the option to pass a detailed string when you need it.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udccb Next steps for you\n\n1. **Open the file** `C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_TravelBot\\HolidayAgent\\Tools\\TavilyTool.py`.\n2. **Locate line\u202f11** (or any `raise HolidayAgentException` statements).\n3. **Either**  \n   * add a second argument (recommended when you have useful debug info), **or**  \n   * change the class definition to make `error_detail` optional (as shown above).\n4. **Save** the file and re\u2011run your script.\n\nIf you still see an error, please copy\u2011paste the updated snippet (the `raise` line and the class definition) and the new traceback, and I\u2019ll help you dig deeper.  \n\n---\n\n### \ud83d\ude4b\u200d\u2640\ufe0f Need anything else?\n\n* Guidance on how to log the extra detail to a file?  \n* A full example of a robust wrapper around the Tavily API?  \n* Anything else in your travel\u2011bot project?\n\nJust let me know! Happy coding, and I hope your holiday\u2011planning bot gets back on track soon. \ud83d\ude80"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Travel_Researcher", "content": "**What the traceback is telling you**\n\n```\nHolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail'\n```\n\nThe custom exception class `HolidayAgentException` is defined to require **two** arguments \u2013 a message and an `error_detail` string \u2013 but somewhere in `TavilyTool.py` (line\u202f11) it is being raised with only the message. Because the second argument is missing, Python raises a `TypeError`.\n\n---\n\n## 1\ufe0f\u20e3 Typical definition of the exception\n\n```python\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, message: str, error_detail: str):\n        super().__init__(message)\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n```\n\nIf you raise it like this:\n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Failed to fetch data\")\n```\n\nyou\u2019ll get exactly the error you saw, because `error_detail` isn\u2019t supplied.\n\n---\n\n## 2\ufe0f\u20e3 Two ways to fix it\n\n### \u2705 Option\u202fA \u2013 Pass the missing argument wherever the exception is raised  \n\nFind every `raise HolidayAgentException(...)` line (the one on line\u202f11 is the culprit) and give it a second argument that provides useful context (e.g., the HTTP status code, the URL that was called, or the original exception message).\n\n**Before (problematic)**  \n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Tavily API request failed\")\n```\n\n**After (fixed)**  \n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\n    \"Tavily API request failed\",\n    error_detail=f\"Status code {response.status_code} \u2013 URL: {url}\"\n)\n```\n\nYou can tailor the `error_detail` string to whatever information will help you debug later.\n\n---\n\n### \u2705 Option\u202fB \u2013 Make the second argument optional  \n\nIf you don\u2019t want to edit every raise\u2011statement, change the exception class so that `error_detail` has a default value. Then existing calls that only pass a message will continue to work.\n\n**Patch the class definition (usually near the top of `TavilyTool.py`):**\n\n```python\n# --------------------------------------------------------------\n#   HolidayAgentException \u2013 make error_detail optional\n# --------------------------------------------------------------\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Custom exception for the HolidayAgent tools.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, message: str, error_detail: str = \"\"):\n        # Initialise the base Exception with the primary message\n        super().__init__(message)\n        # Store any extra detail for logging / debugging\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        # When the exception is printed, show both parts if we have detail\n        base = super().__str__()\n        return f\"{base} | Detail: {self.error_detail}\" if self.error_detail else base\n```\n\nNow you can keep the existing raise\u2011statement:\n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\"Tavily API request failed\")\n```\n\nand, when you *do* have extra context, you can still pass it:\n\n```python\nraise HolidayAgentException(\n    \"Tavily API request failed\",\n    error_detail=f\"Timeout after {timeout}s\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3\ufe0f\u20e3 Quick \u201cpatch\u2011and\u2011run\u201d checklist\n\n1. **Open the file**  \n   `C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_HolidayAgent\\Tools\\TavilyTool.py`\n\n2. **Locate the class definition** (it may be at the top of the file). Replace it with the version from **Option\u202fB** above, **or** keep the original and just add a default value to `error_detail`.\n\n3. **Find the raise line** (line\u202f11 according to the traceback).  \n   - If you chose **Option\u202fA**, edit that line to include a second argument.  \n   - If you chose **Option\u202fB**, you can leave the line as\u2011is.\n\n4. **Save the file**.\n\n5. **Run your script again**. The `HolidayAgentException` should now be instantiated correctly, and the Tavily request will either succeed or raise a more informative exception.\n\n---\n\n## 4\ufe0f\u20e3 Optional: Adding a tiny logger (helps future debugging)\n\nIf you want every `HolidayAgentException` to be automatically logged, you can extend the class a little:\n\n```python\nimport logging\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)   # configure logging elsewhere in your app\n\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, message: str, error_detail: str = \"\"):\n        super().__init__(message)\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n        # Log the error as soon as it\u2019s created\n        logger.error(f\"{message} | Detail: {error_detail}\")\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        base = super().__str__()\n        return f\"{base} | Detail: {self.error_detail}\" if self.error_detail else base\n```\n\nNow every time you raise the exception, you\u2019ll get a line in your log file without having to add explicit `logger.error(...)` calls everywhere.\n\n---\n\n## 5\ufe0f\u20e3 What to do next if you still see an error\n\n1. **Copy\u2011paste the exact traceback** (including the line numbers) after you\u2019ve made the change.  \n2. **Show the surrounding code** (the class definition and the raise line).  \n3. I can then help you pinpoint any remaining mismatches.\n\n---\n\n### \ud83c\udf89 TL;DR\n\n- **Root cause:** `HolidayAgentException` expects two arguments but is raised with one.  \n- **Fix #1:** Add a second argument (`error_detail`) wherever you raise it.  \n- **Fix #2 (easier long\u2011term):** Change the exception class to make `error_detail` optional (`error_detail: str = \"\"`).  \n\nApply either fix, re\u2011run, and the Tavily tool should work again. Let me know if anything else pops up! \ud83d\ude80"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Glad you\u2019ve got the full picture of what\u2019s going wrong.  \nHere\u2019s the **quick\u2011copy\u2011paste fix** you can apply right now, plus a short checklist to verify everything works.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udccb One\u2011line patch (make `error_detail` optional)\n\nAdd/replace the class definition in **`C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_HolidayAgent\\Tools\\TavilyTool.py`** with the code below:\n\n```python\nimport logging\n\n# Configure a logger once in your application entry\u2011point\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)   # (set level/handler elsewhere)\n\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Custom exception for the HolidayAgent tools.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, message: str, error_detail: str = \"\"):\n        # Initialise the base Exception with the primary message\n        super().__init__(message)\n        # Store any extra detail for debugging / logging\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n\n        # Optional: automatically log every raise\n        if logger.handlers:                     # only if logging is configured\n            logger.error(f\"{message} | Detail: {error_detail}\")\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        base = super().__str__()\n        return f\"{base} | Detail: {self.error_detail}\" if self.error_detail else base\n```\n\n### Why this works\n* `error_detail` now has a default value (`\"\"`), so **any existing** `raise HolidayAgentException(\"\u2026\")` statements stay valid.\n* When you *do* want to pass extra context, you still can:\n  ```python\n  raise HolidayAgentException(\n      \"Tavily API request failed\",\n      error_detail=f\"Status {response.status_code} \u2013 URL {url}\"\n  )\n  ```\n\n---\n\n## \u2705 Checklist after applying the patch\n\n1. **Open the file** and replace the old class definition with the snippet above.  \n2. **Save** the file.  \n3. **Run** your script again.  \n   * If the exception is raised, you\u2019ll now see a clear message like:  \n     ```\n     HolidayAgentException: Tavily API request failed | Detail: Status 504 \u2013 URL https://api.tavily.com/\u2026\n     ```\n   * If the request succeeds, the script proceeds without the `TypeError`.  \n4. (Optional) If you want logs written to a file, configure logging in your main module, e.g.:\n\n   ```python\n   import logging\n   logging.basicConfig(\n       filename='holiday_agent.log',\n       level=logging.ERROR,\n       format='%(asctime)s %(levelname)s %(name)s %(message)s'\n   )\n   ```\n\n5. **Test both paths**:  \n   * Force an error (e.g., disconnect internet) to see the detailed log.  \n   * Run a normal request to confirm nothing else breaks.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\ude80 What to do next?\n\n* **If you still see an error**, copy the *exact* traceback (including line numbers) and the surrounding code (the raise line and the class definition) and paste it here \u2013 I\u2019ll help you troubleshoot further.  \n* **If you want to enrich the error detail**, consider passing the original exception message:\n\n  ```python\n  try:\n      response = requests.get(url, timeout=10)\n      response.raise_for_status()\n  except requests.RequestException as exc:\n      raise HolidayAgentException(\n          \"Tavily API request failed\",\n          error_detail=str(exc)\n      )\n  ```\n\n* **If you\u2019d like a tiny wrapper** around the Tavily API that automatically catches and re\u2011raises with this custom exception, let me know and I can sketch that out for you.\n\n---\n\n### TL;DR\n- **Root cause:** `HolidayAgentException` required two args but was called with one.  \n- **Fix:** Make `error_detail` optional (default `\"\"`) or always pass a second argument.  \n- **Implementation:** Replace the class definition with the snippet above; no other code changes needed.\n\nGive it a run and tell me how it goes! \ud83c\udf89"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Travel_Researcher", "content": "I\u2019m sorry, but I\u2019m focused on validating travel itineraries and related travel\u2011planning details. I can\u2019t assist with debugging code or fixing programming errors. If you\u2019d like me to review a travel plan, check attraction details, verify costs, or anything else related to your Goa trip, just let me know!"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Got it! I\u2019m here to help you with anything travel\u2011related\u2014checking itineraries, confirming attraction details, verifying costs, suggesting hotels, and so on. If you\u2019d like me to review your Goa plan (or any other trip), just share the details you have and I\u2019ll make sure everything lines up. Let me know what you need!"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Travel_Researcher", "content": "Sure thing! Just send over the itinerary (or any part of it) you\u2019d like me to review\u2014dates, destinations, activities, hotels, transport, budget, etc.\u2014and I\u2019ll verify that everything is realistic, up\u2011to\u2011date, and fits within your budget. If you don\u2019t have a draft yet, let me know your travel dates, interests, and budget, and I can put together a custom plan for you."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Great! I\u2019m ready to make sure every detail of your trip is realistic, up\u2011to\u2011date, and stays within budget. To give you the most accurate review (or to build a brand\u2011new plan), could you share a few quick details?\n\n| What I need from you | Why it matters |\n|----------------------|----------------|\n| **Travel dates** (e.g., 12\u202fMar\u202f2025\u202f\u2013\u202f15\u202fMar\u202f2025) | Determines weather, peak\u2011season pricing, and attraction opening hours. |\n| **Destination(s)** (city, region, or specific places you want to visit) | Helps me pick the right attractions, transport routes, and hotels. |\n| **Trip length** (number of nights) | Affects pacing of activities and accommodation costs. |\n| **Interests / preferred activities** (beach, culture, adventure, food, nightlife, wildlife, shopping, etc.) | Lets me prioritize the attractions you\u2019ll love most. |\n| **Budget** (total amount you\u2019d like to spend, or a per\u2011day ceiling) | Guides hotel category, dining choices, and optional extras. |\n| **Accommodation preference** (budget, mid\u2011range, luxury; any specific hotel chain or amenity you need) | Ensures the stay matches your comfort level. |\n| **Transport preferences** (rental scooter, private car, public buses, flights between cities, etc.) | Determines the most efficient and cost\u2011effective way to get around. |\n| **Any special requirements** (dietary restrictions, mobility needs, travel with kids/pets, etc.) | Guarantees the plan is fully suitable for you. |\n\n---\n\n### How the review works\n1. **Day\u2011by\u2011day schedule** \u2013 I\u2019ll check timing, travel distances, and opening hours to make sure nothing is rushed or impossible.  \n2. **Attraction details** \u2013 Verify that the sites are still open, entry fees are current, and any required bookings are noted.  \n3. **Hotel & transport** \u2013 Confirm that the suggested properties exist, price ranges are realistic for your dates, and transport options are feasible.  \n4. **Budget breakdown** \u2013 Item\u2011by\u2011item cost estimate (accommodation, food, transport, entry fees, souvenirs) compared against your total budget.  \n5. **Tips & alerts** \u2013 Highlight any seasonal considerations, safety advice, or local events that could affect your trip.\n\n---\n\n### What to do next\n- **If you already have a draft itinerary**: paste the whole plan (or just the sections you\u2019re unsure about) and I\u2019ll flag any issues and suggest improvements.  \n- **If you need a fresh plan**: fill in the table above, and I\u2019ll craft a custom itinerary right away.\n\nLooking forward to your details so we can lock in a smooth, memorable trip! \ud83c\udf34\u2708\ufe0f\ud83d\uddfa\ufe0f"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Travel_Researcher", "content": "Absolutely\u2014let\u2019s get the specifics so I can verify (or build) a spot\u2011on itinerary that stays within your budget and matches your preferences.\n\nPlease fill in the table below (or just give the info in any format you like). The more detail you provide, the more precise the validation will be.\n\n| What I need from you | Your answer |\n|----------------------|-------------|\n| **Travel dates** (e.g., 12\u202fMar\u202f2025\u202f\u2013\u202f15\u202fMar\u202f2025) | |\n| **Destination(s)** (city, region, or specific places you want to visit) | |\n| **Trip length** (number of nights) | |\n| **Interests / preferred activities** (beach, culture, adventure, food, nightlife, wildlife, shopping, etc.) | |\n| **Budget** (total amount you\u2019d like to spend, or a per\u2011day ceiling) | |\n| **Accommodation preference** (budget, mid\u2011range, luxury; any specific hotel chain or amenity you need) | |\n| **Transport preferences** (rental scooter, private car, public buses, flights between cities, etc.) | |\n| **Any special requirements** (dietary restrictions, mobility needs, traveling with kids/pets, etc.) | |\n\nOnce I have these details, I\u2019ll:\n\n1. **Check each attraction** for current opening hours, entry fees, and any booking requirements.  \n2. **Validate travel times & distances** between all stops (using Google Maps).  \n3. **Confirm hotel availability & price** for your dates (via Serper).  \n4. **Calculate a detailed cost breakdown** and compare it to your budget.  \n5. **Spot any scheduling issues** (over\u2011packed days, unrealistic travel windows) and suggest adjustments.  \n\nFeel free to paste an existing draft itinerary instead if you already have one\u2014I'll review it line\u2011by\u2011line. Looking forward to your details!"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-ceee4c9b-76a1-402c-a232-336bd81aa605", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "stop", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": "Sure thing! Just let me kno